
First install the ARM EABI cross compiler that comes with your distro.

Then download and build binutils
  wget http://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/binutils/binutils-2.25.tar.bz2
  bunzip binutils-2.25.tar.bz2
  tar -xf binutils-2.25.tar
  cd binutils-2.25
  ./configure --target=arm-elf --prefix=/root/busybox/binutils
  make
  make install

Get elf2flt
  mkdir elf2flt
  cd elf2flt
  wget https://gfiber.googlesource.com/buildroot/+archive/d5d2851ec024af7fa982e18e72a8104c96d46e3c/toolchain/elf2flt/elf2flt.tar.gz
  gunzip elf2flt.tar.gz
  tar -xf elf2flt.tar
  patch -p1 < elf2flt.patch

Patch and configure it, for me it was
  ./configure --target=arm-elf --with-libbfd=/root/busybox/binutils-2.25/bfd/libbfd.a --with-libiberty=/root/busybox/binutils-2.25/libiberty/libiberty.a --with-bfd-include-dir=/root/busybox/binutils-2.25/bfd/

Then follow the readme of elf2flt and install the binaries elf2flt and
ld-elf2flt where your arm-linux-gnueabi-* binaries are.

(rename arm-linux-gnueabi-ld to arm-linux-gnueabi-ld.real then copy
ld-elf2flt to arm-linux-gnueabi-ld and elf2flt to arm-linux-gnueabi-elf2flt)

Then you should be able to compile that assembly file.

